%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Govt%20Refuses%20to%20Give%20Clarity%20on%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%20One%20Election%E2%80%99%20Deadline%3B%20Congress%20MPs%20Seek%20Details%20on%20Committee%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16163914%2F2048px-BMC_Election_2012_-_Ink_mark_after_voting_6886404209.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20has%20refused%20to%20provide%20a%20clear%20answer%20to%20three%20Congress%20MPs%20on%20whether%20it%20has%20given%20a%20fixed%20deadline%20to%20the%20high-level%20committee%2C%20under%20former%20president%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%2C%20to%20submit%20its%20report%20on%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98one%20nation%20one%20election%E2%80%99%20theory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20starred%20question%20was%20jointly%20raised%20by%20Congress%20Lok%20Sabha%20MPs%20Adoor%20Prakash%2C%20Anto%20Antony%2C%20and%20Su.%20Thirunavukkarasar%20to%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice.%20They%20also%20sought%20more%20details%20on%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20theory%20of%20%E2%80%98one%20nation%20one%20election%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20advocated%20by%20leaders%20of%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%2C%20including%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20government%20had%20remained%20tight-lipped%20about%20any%20move%20in%20that%20direction%20for%20quite%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20things%20began%20to%20move%20in%20that%20direction%20in%20August-end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20described%20a%20meeting%20between%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20Minister%20of%20State%20(Independent%20Charge)%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20with%20Kovind%20at%20his%20residence%20at%20the%20end%20of%20August%20as%20%E2%80%98a%20courtesy%20call%E2%80%99%2C%20on%20September%201%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fgovt-working-on-logistics-modalities-for-panel-on-one-nation-one-election%2Farticleshow%2F103444062.cms%5C%22%3Enotified%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20committee%20led%20by%20the%20former%20president%20to%20look%20into%20the%20possibility%20of%20simultaneous%20parliamentary%20and%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notification%20on%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20eight-member%20committee%20drew%20media%20attention%2C%20particularly%20because%20it%20came%20just%20days%20before%20the%20Parliament%20was%20to%20be%20in%20a%20special%20session%20(between%20September%2018%20and%2022)%20with%20the%20government%20not%20announcing%20any%20particular%20agenda%20for%20it.%20It%20was%20also%20the%20time%20when%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20was%20finalising%20the%20schedule%20for%20the%20assembly%20elections%20in%20five%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20September%201%20notification%20said%20that%20aside%20from%20Kovind%2C%20the%20committee%20would%20have%20Shah%20too.%20Opposition%20leader%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20and%20former%20Congress%20leader%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%2C%20now%20seen%20close%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20were%20also%20named%20as%20members.%20Former%20Finance%20Commission%20chairman%20N.K.%20Singh%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Harish%20Salve%2C%20former%20secretary%20general%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Subhash%20Kashyap%2C%20and%20former%20chief%20vigilance%20commissioner%20Sanjay%20Kothari%20were%20the%20other%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Chowdhury%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fadhir-ranjan-chowdhury-declines-to-be-on-one-nation-one-election-panel-as-cong-attacks-modi-govt-move%2Farticleshow%2F103314580.cms%5C%22%3Erefused%20to%20be%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20tailor-made%20to%20reach%20certain%20conclusions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2023%2C%20Kovind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fformer-president-ram-nath-kovind-first-meeting-high-level-panel-synchronised-polls-2439631-2023-09-23%5C%22%3Echaired%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20first%20meeting%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20during%20which%20it%20decided%20to%20invite%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20Law%20Commission%20to%20seek%20their%20views%20on%20the%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Law%20Commission%2C%20on%20October%2023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Flaw-commission-presents-roadmap-on-one-nation-one-election-to-ram-nath-kovind-led-panel%2Farticle67459227.ece%5C%22%3Esuggested%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20roadmap%20to%20the%20Kovind%20committee%20on%20how%20to%20proceed%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%208%2C%20while%20replying%20to%20the%20queries%20put%20up%20by%20the%20Congress%20MPs%2C%20the%20law%20ministry%2C%20in%20a%20written%20reply%2C%20avoided%20answering%20whether%20any%20fixed%20term%20had%20been%20set%20for%20the%20committee%20to%20submit%20its%20report.%20Its%20written%20statement%20only%20gave%20the%20objectives%20of%20the%20committee%20and%20also%20justified%20its%20action%20by%20banking%20on%20the%20precedent%20of%20parliamentary%20and%20assembly%20polls%20%E2%80%9Cmostly%20held%20simultaneously%20from%201951-52%20to%201967%2C%20after%20which%20this%20cycle%20got%20broken%E2%80%9D.%20Due%20to%20elections%20being%20organised%20every%20one%20or%20two%20years%2C%20it%20leads%20to%20more%20expenditure%2C%20diversion%20of%20manpower%2C%20including%20security%20forces%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdisruption%20of%20development%20work%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20arguments%20have%20been%20publicly%20stated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20too%2C%20even%20prior%20to%20forming%20the%20Kovind-led%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20statement%20in%20Parliament%2C%20the%20law%20ministry%20referred%20to%20the%20parliamentary%20standing%20committ