s%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F06162412%2Ffile-michel.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELondon%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20The%20plot%20has%20thickened%20%3Ci%3Evis-a-vis%3C%2Fi%3E%20a%20British%20arms%20consultant%20Christian%20Michel%20being%20in%20detention%20in%20India%20without%20a%20trial%20for%20an%20extended%20period.%20This%20week%2C%20he%20completed%20five%20years%20in%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20a%20decade%20of%20inquiry%2C%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20in%20India%20pleads%20it%20has%20yet%20to%20complete%20its%20probe%20and%20needs%20to%20file%20another%20%E2%80%98supplementary%E2%80%99%20chargesheet.%20It%20also%20appeared%20to%20blame%20an%20unresolved%20issue%20with%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20Serious%20Fraud%20Office%20(SFO)%20as%20one%20of%20the%20causes%20of%20the%20delay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20436A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%20provides%20for%20the%20release%20of%20an%20accused%20after%20he%20has%20undergone%20detention%20%E2%80%98for%20a%20period%20extending%20up%20to%20one-half%20of%20the%20maximum%20period%20of%20imprisonment%E2%80%99%2C%20other%20than%20in%20exceptional%20circumstances.%20If%20found%20guilty%20under%20the%20offences%20for%20which%20he%20was%20extradited%2C%20Michel%20is%20likely%20to%20receive%20a%20maximum%20sentence%20of%20seven%20years%20(the%20maximum%20term%20of%20imprisonment%20for%20an%20offence%20under%20Section%20420%20IPC)%2C%20which%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20standard%20remission%2C%20would%20have%20entitled%20him%20to%20a%20discharge%20by%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20opposed%20this%20argument%20because%2C%20in%20a%20supplementary%20chargesheet%2C%20Michel%20was%20accused%20under%20Section%20467%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%2C%20which%20carries%20a%20life%20sentence%2C%20if%20convicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichel%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20Aljo%20Joseph%20has%20maintained%20in%20court%20that%20this%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20Section%2021%20of%20the%20Extradition%20Act%2C%20which%20upholds%20a%20%E2%80%98doctrine%20of%20speciality%E2%80%99%2C%20emphasising%20that%20no%20new%20charges%20can%20be%20added%20to%20the%20ones%20which%20constitute%20the%20basis%20of%20an%20extradition%20request%20%E2%80%93%20in%20this%20case%2C%20the%20one%20by%20India%20to%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20(UAE).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20an%20order%20on%20February%207%20this%20year%2C%20a%20three-member%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%2C%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fagustawestland-vvip-chopper-scam-case-supreme-court-rejects-christian-michels-bail-plea%2Farticleshow%2F97695652.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20Michel%E2%80%99s%20bail%20petition%20%E2%80%98under%20the%20provisions%20of%20Section%20436A%2C%20cannot%20be%20accepted%20as%20valid%E2%80%99%20since%20Section%20467%20carries%20a%20maximum%20sentence%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20citing%20Article%2017%20of%20the%20Extradition%20Treaty%20between%20India%20and%20the%20UAE%2C%20the%20judges%20decreed%20%E2%80%98it%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20person%20to%20be%20extradited%20shall%20not%20be%20tried%20or%20punished%20in%20the%20requesting%20State%20(namely%20India)%20except%20for%20the%20offences%20for%20which%20his%20extradition%20is%20sought%20or%20for%20offences%20connected%20therewith%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20Section%2021%20of%20the%20Indian%20Extradition%20Act%2C%201962%2C%20the%20judges%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20stated%20that%20an%20extradited%20person%20shall%20not%20be%20tried%20in%20India%20for%20an%20offence%20other%20than%3A%20%E2%80%98(a)%20the%20extradition%20offence%20in%20relation%20to%20which%20he%20was%20surrendered%20or%20returned%3B%20or%20(b)%20any%20lesser%20offence%20disclosed%20by%20the%20facts%20proved%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20securing%20his%20surrender%20or%20return%20other%20than%20an%20offence%20in%20relation%20to%20which%20an%20order%20for%20his%20surrender%20for%20return%20could%20not%20be%20lawfully%20made%3B%20or%20(c)%20the%20offence%20in%20respect%20of%20which%20the%20foreign%20State%20has%20given%20its%20consent.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20it%20squared%20this%20circle%20is%20not%20clear.%20The%20bench%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20whether%20the%20CBI%20has%20fulfilled%20the%20requirements%20of%20the%20treaty%20with%20the%20UAE%20and%20the%20Extradition%20Act%2C%20while%20merely%20saying%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20petitioner%20is%20alleged%20to%20have%20committed%20offences%20under%20Section%20467%20IPC%20which%20is%20punishable%20with%20up%20to%20life%20imprisonment%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20dismissing%20his%20bail%20plea%2C%20it%20clarified%20that%20Michel%20could%20move%20the%20trial%20court%20afresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png-300x150.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png-1024x512.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png-800x400.png%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670931%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Photo%3A%20Pinakpani%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBartered%20for%20Latifa%20abduction%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFairly%20late%20at%20night%20on%20December%204%2C%202018%2C%20a%20private%20jet%20landed%20in%20Delhi%20from%20Dubai.%20It%20carried%20as%20one%20of%20its%20passengers%20a%20blindfolded%20and%20handcuffed%20Michel.%20He%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvvip-chopper-case-christian-michel-sent-to-five-day-cbi-custody-by-delhi-court%5C%22%3Eaccused%20by%20the%20CBI%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20paying%20bribes%20to%20Congress%20party%20leaders%20to%20clinch%20a%20VVIP%20helicopter%20deal%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%20in%202010.%20Michel%20denies%20the%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20record%2C%20the%20original%20approval%20in%20principle%20for%20the%20choice%20of%20choppers%20was%20given%20by%20Brajesh%20Mishra%2C%20principal%20secretary%20to%20BJP%20Prime%20Minister%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20and%20the%20Indian%20National%20Security%20Adviser%20around%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%20and%20June%202016%2C%20the%20SFO%20in%20response%20to%20a%20CBI%20request%20despatched%20some%20documents%20connected%20with%20the%20Michel%20case.%20Soon%20after%2C%20the%20SFO%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20communicated%20to%20the%20CBI%20that%20the%20information%20had%20been%20shared%20by%20mistake%20and%20that%20it%20could%20not%20be%20disclosed%20under%20any%20circumstances.%20The%20SFO%20further%20indicated%20that%20double%20jeopardy%20could%20arise%20by%20doing%20so.%20Michel%20had%20on%20the%20same%20matter%20been%20exonerated%20by%20the%20Italian%20judiciary%2C%20where%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20was%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgustaWestland%2C%20the%20England-based%20makers%20of%20the%20helicopters%2C%20was%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20an%20Italian%20company%20Finmeccanica%2C%20now%20Leonardo%20S.p.A.%20Two%20of%20its%20Rome-based%20executives%20were%20accused%20of%20paying%20bribes%20to%20Indian%20officials%20for%20the%20contract%3B%20but%20were%20eventually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcbi-rubbishes-italian-court-ruling-that-found-no-graft-in-vvip-chopper-case%5C%22%3Edeclared%20innocent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20respect%20of%20the%20allegation%20against%20Michel%2C%20an%20Italian%20judge%20said%20this%20was%20no%20more%20than%20a%20%E2%80%98hypothesis%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2018%20last%2C%20in%20a%20written%20submission%20to%20Arvind%20Kumar%2C%20a%20judge%20in%20a%20special%20CBI%20court%2C%20the%20CBI%20reiterated%20that%20the%20SFO%20had%20stressed%20to%20it%20that%20%E2%80%98the%20evidence%20transmitted%20should%20not%20have%20been%20sent%E2%80%99%2C%20that%20%E2%80%98it%20should%20not%20be%20used%20in%20any%20investigation%20or%20prosecution%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98the%20evidence%20remains%20confidential%20and%20is%20not%20to%20be%20disclosed%20or%20used%20until%20they%20(the%20SFO)%20resolve%20the%20issue%20or%20until%20further%20notice%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20judge%20accepts%20that%2C%20then%20there%20can%20potentially%20be%20no%20progress%20without%20a%20resolution%20by%20the%20SFO%3B%20and%20Michel%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20behind%20bars%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%20without%20a%20trial.%20He%20has%20consistently%20been%20refused%20bail%2C%20despite%20all%20other%20accused%20in%20the%20case%2C%20including%20a%20former%20Air%20Chief%20Marshall%20S.P.%20Tyagi%2C%20being%20conditionally%20set%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotwithstanding%20the%20SFO%20imposing%20strict%20confidentiality%20on%20the%20CBI%2C%20%3Ci%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fi%3E%20on%20January%2015%2C%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fuk-shares-crucial-info-but-with-a-rider-cbi%2Farticleshow%2F88905199.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20with%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20matter%20told%20%3Ci%3EET%3C%2Fi%3E%20the%20information%20(from%20the%20SFO)%20related%20to%20monies%20sent%20by%20AgustaWestland%20to%20Michel%20as%20%E2%80%98commission%E2%80%99%2C%20to%20swing%20the%20VVIP%20chopper%20deal%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20British%20company.%E2%80%9D%20It%20further%20maintained%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20information%20assumes%20significance%20since%20it%20establishes%20monies%20paid%20by%20AgustaWestland%20to%20Michel%20who%20allegedly%20in%20turn%20paid%20kickbacks%20to%20influential%20people%20in%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20secure%20the%20deal%2C%20said%20the%20people%20cited%20earlier%20(namely%20%E2%80%98people%20with%20direct%20knowledge%E2%80%99).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2017%20last%2C%20in%20seeking%20disclosure%20of%20the%20SFO%20documents%2C%20Michel%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20Joseph%20had%20cited%20before%20judge%20Kumar%20that%20the%20document%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpublished%20way%20back%20on%2015.01.2022%20in%20a%20newspaper.%20In%20these%20circumstances%20as%20per%20the%20law%20and%20the%20procedure%20such%20documents%20cannot%20be%20kept%20in%20secret%20in%20view%20of%20the%20Section%20172%20%26amp%3B%20207%20of%20the%20CrPC%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20special%20public%20prosecutor%20D.P.%20Singh%20rejected%20the%20suggestion%20of%20a%20leak%20to%20the%20newspaper%20by%20replying%20that%20the%20article%20%E2%80%98only%20records%20the%20court%20proceedings%2C%20which%20are%20open%20in%20terms%20of%20Section%20327%20CrPC%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20indication%20of%20the%20CBI%20violating%20the%20embargo%20created%E2%80%99.%20He%20avoided%20addressing%20the%20aspect%20of%20%3Ci%3EET%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%99s%20piece%20referring%20to%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20with%20direct%20knowledge%E2%80%9D%20as%20its%20sources%2C%20which%20was%20patently%20not%20a%20reporting%20of%20a%20court%20proceeding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SFO%20was%20asked%20to%20clarify%20its%20position%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20%3Ci%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fi%3E%20report%20and%20whether%2C%20since%20Michel%20was%20cleared%20by%20Italian%20courts%2C%20he%20can%20be%20accused%20or%20tried%20for%20the%20same%20alleged%20crime%20twice.%20It%20was%20considering%20its%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20in%20August%20this%20year%20before%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20Delhi%2C%20which%20this%20writer%20has%20accessed%2C%20Michel%20demanded%20he%20uphold%20international%20law%20and%20confront%20Narendra%20Modi.%20He%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20a%20political%20prisoner%20of%20Mr%20Modi.%E2%80%9D%20He%20also%20described%20himself%20as%20%E2%80%98a%20judicial%20hostage%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20and%20lamented%20that%20he%20%E2%80%98will%20never%20be%20taken%20to%20trial%20ever%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetailing%20his%20ordeal%2C%20he%20alleged%20that%20he%20was%20interrogated%20%E2%80%98for%20300%20hours%2C%2012%20hours%20a%20day%E2%80%99%20by%20%E2%80%98three%20teams%20in%20rotation%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20his%20third%20letter%20to%20Sunak.%20None%20of%20which%20has%2C%20according%20to%20informed%20persons%2C%20been%20replied%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202020%2C%20a%20United%20Nations%20Working%20Group%20on%20Arbitrary%20Detention%20(UNWGAD)%20ruled%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20deprivation%20of%20liberty%20of%20Christian%20James%20Michel%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20being%20in%20contravention%20of%20the%20articles%203%2C%209%2C%2010%20and%2011(1)%20of%20the%20Universal%20Declaration%20of%20Human%20Rights%20and%20articles%209(3)%3B%2010(1)%3B%20and%2014(10)-(2)%20and%2030(b)-(d)%20and%20(g)%20of%20the%20International%20Covenant%20on%20Civil%20and%20Political%20Rights%2C%20is%20arbitrary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichel%20complained%20that%20despite%20the%20UNWGAD%20asking%20for%20his%20immediate%20release%2C%20the%20British%20government%20failed%20to%20secure%20his%20freedom.%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20your%20government%20playing%20these%20dirty%20little%20games%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked%20Sunak.%20%E2%80%9CPrime%20Minister%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20the%20problem%20I%20have%20had%20with%20your%20government.%20Is%20it%20corruption%2C%20rampant%20power%20lust%2C%20or%20just%20lack%20of%20competence%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%2C%20then%2C%20asserted%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20Prime%20Minister%20have%20nearly%20your%20entire%20fortune%20%5Bactually%20the%20value%20of%20his%20wife%20Akshata%20Murthy%E2%80%99s%20shares%5D%20invested%20in%20INFOSYS%20India.%20Some%20%C2%A3500%2C000%2C000.%20You%20know%20that%20if%20Modi%20once%20does%20not%20like%20the%20way%20you%20look%20at%20him%2C%20he%20will%20order%20an%20ED%20%5BIndian%20Enforcement%20Directorate%5D%20raid%20on%20INFOSYS%2C%20quote%20%E2%80%98due%20process%E2%80%99%20as%20he%20did%20to%20the%20BBC%20%26amp%3B%20wipe%20out%20your%20share%20value.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%E2%80%99s%20office%20refused%20to%20comment.%20A%20British%20Foreign%20Office%20spokesman%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9COur%20staff%20continue%20to%20support%20Mr%20Michel%20and%20raise%20his%20case%20with%20the%20Indian%20authorities%20at%20every%20appropriate%20opportunity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F08103202%2FRishi_Sunak_Official_Cabinet_Portrait_September_2021.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F08103202%2FRishi_Sunak_Official_Cabinet_Portrait_September_2021.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F08103202%2FRishi_Sunak_Official_Cabinet_Portrait_September_2021-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F08103202%2FRishi_Sunak_Official_Cabinet_Portrait_September_2021-1024x684.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-643221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EUK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak.%20Photo%3A%20Simon%20Dawson%2FNo%2010%20Downing%20Street%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Michel%E2%80%99s%20bail%20applications%20was%2C%20indeed%2C%20supported%20by%20the%20British%20High%20Commission%20in%20Delhi.%20The%20petition%20to%20the%20CBI%20judge%20pointed%20to%20his%20ill%20health%20brought%20about%20by%20his%20prolonged%20and%20allegedly%20inhuman%20incarceration.%20In%202021%2C%20Michel%20wrote%20to%20the%20then%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Boris%20Johnson%3A%20%E2%80%9CDue%20to%20the%20heat%20and%20lack%20of%20water%20I%20got%20three%20kidney%20stones.%20I%20got%20e-coli%20from%20the%20water%20when%20I%20caught%20Covid%2019.%E2%80%9D%20The%20judge%20did%20not%20take%20kindly%20to%20the%20British%20intervention%20and%20turned%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Michel%20appealed%20to%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20for%20interim%20bail%20to%20avoid%20COVID-19%20in%20a%20crowded%20prison%2C%20the%20verdict%20was%20that%20%E2%80%98foreign%20nationals%20will%20not%20be%20considered%20for%20interim%20bail%20under%20any%20criteria%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20the%20UAE%2C%20of%20which%20Dubai%20is%20a%20part%2C%20declined%20to%20extradite%20Michel%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20evidence%20presented%20in%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20request.%20But%20a%20%3Ci%3Evolte%20face%3C%2Fi%3E%20occurred.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20April%202018%2C%E2%80%9D%20Michel%20indicated%20to%20Johnson%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20warned%20by%20the%20Dubai%20prosecutor%20that%20a%20deal%20had%20been%20done%20with%20India%20to%20exchange%20me%20(in%20lieu%20of%20the%20Dubai%20ruler%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20Princess%20Latifa%2C%20who%20had%20escaped%20from%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20clutches%20to%20seek%20asylum%20in%20India%2C%20being%20captured%20by%20Indian%20armed%20forces%20in%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%20and%20returned%20to%20her%20father)%20and%20I%20should%20go%20back%20to%20the%20UK.%20I%20had%20my%20passport%20%26amp%3B%20I%20should%20have%20run.%20But%20I%20was%20done%20running%20from%20Modi.%20If%20they%20were%20going%20to%20rendition%20me%20so%20be%20it.%E2%80%9D%20Both%20the%20London%20High%20Court%20and%20the%20UNWGAD%20upheld%20this%20version%20of%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchistian-michel-boris-johnson-letter-modi-princess-latifa%5C%22%3Efurther%20conveyed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Johnson%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20mid-May%20(2018)%20I%20%26amp%3B%20my%20lawyers%20were%20called%20to%20meet%20with%20a%20delegation%20of%20UAE%20officials%20led%20by%20Colonel%20Waleed%20of%20the%20Dubai%20CID%20%26amp%3B%20Rakesh%20Asthana%20special%20director%20CBI%20India.%20Over%20three%20separate%20meetings%20over%20two%20weeks%20in%20front%20of%20%26amp%3B%20with%20the%20UAE%20officials%E2%80%99%20support%20and%20blessings%20%26amp%3B%20in%20front%20of%20my%20lawyers%2C%20openly%20without%20any%20concern%20for%20UAE%2C%20international%20law%20or%20my%20human%20rights%2C%20(Asthana)%20said%20that%20unless%20I%20implicate%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20her%20son%20%26amp%3B%20the%20senior%20opposition%20leader%20Ahmed%20Patel%20in%20corruption%2C%20I%20would%20be%20taken%20to%20India%20(renditioned)%20%26amp%3B%20out%20in%20jail%20for%20a%20long%20time%20without%20bail.%20They%20said%20no%20one%20will%20save%20you%20%26amp%3B%20mentioned%20some%20names%20%26amp%3B%20said%20a%20deal%20has%20been%20done.%20It%20was%20made%20clear%20to%20my%20lawyers%20%26amp%3B%20I%20that%20I%20was%20to%20be%20swapped%20for%20Latifa.%20My%20lawyers%20were%20shocked.%20If%20I%20agreed%2C%20I%20would%20be%20made%20a%20witness%20%26amp%3B%20would%20not%20have%20to%20go%20to%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichel%20continues%20to%20languish%20in%20Tihar.%20In%202013%2C%20the%20UPA%20defence%20minister%20A.K.%20Antony%2C%20in%20a%20state%20of%20saintly%20panic%2C%20referred%20the%20matter%20to%20the%20CBI%2C%20following%20the%20accusations%20against%20Finmeccanica%20executives%20in%20Italy.%20The%20CBI%20filed%20a%20chargesheet%20in%20the%20case%20in%202017%20and%20a%20supplementary%20chargesheet%20in%202020%3B%20and%20persistently%20begs%20for%20more%20time%20before%20the%20CBI%20judge%20for%20further%20investigation.%20It%20is%20also%20a%20fact%20that%20Michel%E2%80%99s%20family%20have%20not%20pressured%20the%20British%20Foreign%20Office%20to%20the%20extent%20the%20husband%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2Fmar%2F16%2Fnazanin-zaghari-ratcliffe-to-leave-iran-after-six-years-in-detention-reports%5C%22%3ENazanin%20Zaghari-Ratcliffe%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20when%20she%20was%20detained%20in%20Iran%20from%202016%20to%202022.%20By%20any%20standards%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20an%20instance%20of%20grave%20injustice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFormerly%20editor-at-large%20of%20CNN%2C%20London-based%20Ashis%20Ray%20is%20the%20longest-serving%20Indian%20foreign%20correspondent.%20He%20can%20be%20followed%20%40ashiscray%20on%20X.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702043706000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F06162412%2Ffile-michel.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchristian-michel-jail-five-years%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20accused%20in%20the%20Agusta%20Westland%20helicopter%20deal%2C%20the%20British%20national's%20letters%20to%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20have%20been%20to%20no%20avail.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchristian-michel-jail-five-years%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prince%20Harry%20loses%20bid%20to%20have%20publisher's%20libel%20defence%20thrown%20out%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22