com%2Felon-musk-children%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20pair%20have%20three%20children%20together%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20X%2C%20Exa%2C%20and%20Tau.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Melcher%2C%20a%20California%20family%20law%20attorney%20and%20partner%20at%20Walzer%20Melcher%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Musk%20may%20have%20included%20that%20claim%20in%20his%20filing%20to%20influence%20the%20Texas%20judge's%20opinion%20of%20Grimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20the%20extent%20that%20she%20was%20told%20that%20information%20%E2%80%94%20both%20courts%2C%20Texas%20and%20California%2C%20use%20the%20same%20standards%20for%20determining%20child%20custody%20matters%2C%20which%20is%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20meaning%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20custody%2C%20there's%20no%20reason%20she'd%20do%20better%20in%20California%20than%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-grimes-moving-california-avoid-texas-court-custody-battle-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshe%20would%20almost%20certainly%20fare%20better%20in%20California%20than%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20child%20support%2C%20Melcher%20said%2C%20citing%20the%20two%20states'%20differing%20child%20support%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Texas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mcnamaralawyers.com%2Fservices%2Fchild-support-attorney%2Fcalculating-maximum-child-support-texas%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecaps%20monthly%20child%20support%20payments%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20%242%2C760%20for%20three%20children%2C%20California%20does%20not%20have%20a%20limit%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20Musk%20could%20be%20required%20to%20pay%20a%20much%20larger%20amount.%20The%20Tesla%20CEO%2C%20one%20of%20the%20richest%20people%20in%20the%20world%2C%20currently%20has%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20about%20%24222%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fbillionaires%2Fprofiles%2Felon-r-musk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBloomberg%20Billionaires%20Index.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20unclear%20if%20the%20case%20will%20ultimately%20result%20in%20child%20support%20orders%2C%20family%20law%20experts%20said%20that%20would%20explain%20why%20both%20Musk%20and%20Grimes%20are%20fighting%20so%20hard%20over%20where%20the%20case%20plays%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20M.%20Walzer%2C%20a%20California%20family%20law%20attorney%20and%20partner%20at%20Walzer%20Melcher%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20did%20not%20think%20the%20claim%20that%20Grimes%20told%20Musk%20she%20heard%20California%20would%20be%20better%20for%20her%20was%20especially%20damaging%2C%20noting%20it's%20already%20apparent%20the%20two%20are%20fighting%20over%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20for%20Musk%20and%20Grimes%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETexas%20v.%20California%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20said%20in%C2%A0his%20amended%20complaint%20filed%20this%20week%20that%C2%A0he%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusk-asked-for-relationship-grimes-kids-in-secret-lawsuit-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%20legal%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0against%20Grimes%20in%20September%20after%20she%20took%20their%20two%20youngest%20children%20to%20California%20and%20he%20realized%20she%20did%20not%20plan%20to%20return.%20That%20same%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrimes-sues-elon-musk-parental-relationship-children-petition-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGrimes%20responded%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Musk's%20Texas%20lawsuit%20with%20a%20countersuit%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20petition%20said%20that%20Grimes%20described%20their%20custody%20agreement%20in%20an%20enrollment%20packet%20for%20one%20of%20their%20children's%20daycare%20programs%20on%20August%204.%20According%20to%20Musk%2C%20Grimes%20said%20the%20pair%20have%20a%20%26quot%3B2%20week%202%20week%20agreement%26quot%3B%20if%20they're%20%26quot%3Bnot%20getting%20along%26quot%3B%20or%20they're%20not%20in%20the%20same%20city%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20they'd%20split%20time%20with%20the%20children%2050%2F50.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20live%20in%20separate%20houses%20but%20we%20are%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20reads.%20%26quot%3BHowever%20custody%20can%20be%20tricky%20as%20I%20work%20in%20SF%20and%20Dad%20works%20in%20Texas.%20We%20try%20to%20spend%20as%20much%20time%20as%20possible%20in%20each%20others%20city.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20suit%2C%20Musk%20has%20called%20for%20Grimes%20to%20bring%20their%20youngest%20children%20back%20to%20Texas%2C%20while%20Grimes%20claims%20in%20her%20own%20he%20has%20X%20in%20the%20state%20over%20her%20objection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20also%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20issue%20a%20temporary%20order%20that%20would%20designate%20him%20as%20the%20sole%20managing%20conservator%20of%20the%20children.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Musk%20would%20be%20given%20primary%20control%20over%20most%20decisions%20involving%20the%20children%20%E2%80%94%20from%20where%20they%20live%20and%20what%20schools%20they%20attend%20to%20their%20medical%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalzer%20said%20it%20would%20be%20unusual%20for%20a%20parent%20to%20be%20named%20the%20sole%20managing%20conservator%20unless%20there%20were%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20other%20parent%2C%20such%20as%20allegations%20of%20child%20abuse%20or%20substance%20abuse.%20However%2C%20there's%20no%20evidence%20Musk%20has%20such%20concerns%20about%20Grimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20billionaire%20has%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20award%20Grimes%20a%20standard%20possession%20schedule%20for%20seeing%20the%20children%2C%20which%20would%20allow%20the%20singer%20to%20have%20the%20kids%20on%20the%20fir