22%3E908%20days.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223998%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20picture%20shows%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%20X37B%20being%20loaded%20into%20its%20cargo%20hold.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6572ef700ec98e92f74d64ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225740%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EX37B%20is%20shown%20preparing%20for%20its%20next%20launch.%20It%20is%20sporting%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%20logo%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20US%20Space%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20run%20by%20NASA%2C%20the%20project%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2F25275-x37b-space-plane.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520Brief%2520History%2520of%2520the%2520X%252D37B%26amp%3Btext%3DNASA%2520transferred%2520the%2520project%2520to%2Ccarry%2520and%2520free%252Dflight%2520tests.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecame%20classified%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20was%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20Defense%20Advanced%20Research%20Projects%20Agency%20(DARPA)%20in%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202020%2C%20the%20missions%20have%20been%20run%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-force-orbital-warfare-unit-in-charge-x37b-space-plane-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20US%20Space%20Force%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20government's%20space-defense%20branch%20of%20the%20military%20formalized%20by%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226194%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22X37B%20is%20shown%20landed%20on%20the%20tarmac.%20A%20person%20in%20protective%20gear%20is%20shown%20walking%20in%20front%20of%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6572f0ae7a3c8094d5dae583%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224161%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EX37B%20shown%20here%20after%20its%20sixth%20orbital%20flight%20mission.%3Cp%3EUS%20Space%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20statement%20from%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%20noted%20that%20X-37B%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Boperating%20in%20new%20orbital%20regimes%26quot%3B%20during%20this%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EX-37B%20will%20be%20riding%20to%20space%20on%20top%20of%20SpaceX's%20Falcon%20Heavy%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20Falcon%20Heavy%20is%20the%20world's%20second%20most%20powerful%20operational%20rocket.%20It%20offers%20three%20times%20more%20lift%20than%20the%20Falcon%209%20and%20Atlas%205%2C%20the%20crafts%20that%20previously%20launched%20the%20X-37B%20missions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newscientist.com%2Farticle%2F2407092-space-forces-secretive-space-plane-is-making-its-highest-flight-yet%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOver%2520the%2520course%2520of%2520its%2Cthe%2520six%2520at%2520908%2520days.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20Scientist%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltogether%2C%20this%20suggests%20that%20X-37B%20could%20attempt%20to%20reach%20higher%20and%20fly%20longer%20than%20ever%20before%20during%20its%20seventh%20flight%2C%20New%20Scientist%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20excited%20to%20expand%20the%20envelope%20of%20the%20reusable%20X-37B's%20capabilities%2C%20using%20the%20flight-proven%20service%20module%20and%20Falcon%20Heavy%20rocket%20to%20fly%20multiple%20cutting-edge%20experiments%20for%20the%20Department%20of%20the%20Air%20Force%20and%20its%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lieutenant%20Colonel%20Joseph%20Fritschen%2C%20the%20X-37B%20Program%20Director%2C%20in%20a%20statement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225140%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22SpaceX's%20Falcon%20Heavy%20rocket%20is%20shown%20taking%20off%2C%20leaving%20behind%20if%20flames%20and%20vapor.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6572f44258e7c0c29a2ae8ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222945%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpaceX's%20Falcon%20Heavy%20takes%20off%20on%20Oct.%2013%2C%202023%20from%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20carrying%20NASA's%20Psyche%20mission%20payload.%3Cp%3ERicardo%20Ramirez%20Buxeda%2FOrlando%20Sentinel%2FTribune%20News%20Service%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20all%20goes%20to%20plan%2C%20this%20mission%20will%20add%20to%20the%20spaceplanes'%20impressive%20flight%20time.%20Since%20first%20launched%20in%20April%202010%2C%20X37B%20have%20accrued%20more%20than%203%2C770%20days%20in%20space%2C%20per%20the%20Space%20Force's%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20known%20X-37Bs%20in%20operation%2C%20developed%20in%20partnership%20with%20Boeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20upcoming%20flight%2C%20dubbed%20OTV-7%2C%20X-37B%20will%20carry%20%26quot%3Bgroundbreaking%26quot%3B%20experiments%20that%20will%20%26quot%3Bequip%20the%20United%20States%20with%20the%20knowledge%20to%20enhance%20current%20and%20future%20space%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20General%20B.%20Chance%20Saltzman%2C%20Chief%20of%20Space%20Operations%20at%20Space%20Force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20a%20NASA%20experiment%20to%20study%20the%20effect%20of%20long-term%20cosmic%20radiation%20exposure%20on%20seeds%20brought%20in%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20experiment%20will%20test%20%26quot%3Bfuture%20space%20domain%20awareness%20technologies%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20statement.%20The%20exact%20nature%20of%20this%20cargo%20was%20not%20disclosed%2C%20but%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20relate%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssc.spaceforce.mil%2FProgram-Executive-Offices%2FSpace-Domain-Awareness-Combat-Power%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSpace%2520Domain%2520Awareness%2520%2526%2520Combat%2520Power%2520is%2520the%2520Space%2520Systems%2520Command%2Cwhile%2520also%2520providing%2520National%2520Security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetection%20and%20monitoring%20of%20crafts%3C%2Fa%3E%20floating%20around%20the%20Earth%20that%20could%20threaten%20national%20or%20commercial%20space