e%2C%20even%20though%20he%20represented%20a%20district%20partially%20on%20Long%20Island%20%E2%80%94%20reportedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorge-santos-made-more-2-days-cameo-than-congress-salary-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emade%20more%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20platform%20in%20two%20days%20than%20he%20did%20in%20a%20year%20in%20Congress%2C%20where%20he%20held%20a%20job%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorge-santos-expelled-congress-what-happens-next-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20historic%20expulsion%20last%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFortunately%20for%20Santos%2C%20he%20can%20probably%20keep%20that%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20has%20a%20%26quot%3BSon%20of%20Sam%26quot%3B%20law%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20state%20and%20criminal%20victims%20to%20block%20people%20convicted%20of%20crimes%20from%20profiting%20from%20their%20misdeeds.%20Santos%20is%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.nyed.497085%2Fgov.uscourts.nyed.497085.50.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%2023-count%20indictment%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20an%20array%20of%20alleged%20crimes%20related%20to%20his%20congressional%20campaign's%20finances.%20Santos%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%20the%20charges%20and%20is%20set%20to%20go%20to%20trial%20in%20September%3B%20his%20attorney%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20The%20charges%20against%20Santos%20%E2%80%94%20plus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhats-in-house-ethics-committee-report-george-santos-expulsion-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20damning%20and%20embarrassing%20House%20Ethics%20Committee%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20found%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorge-santos-campaign-money-onlyfans-hermes-botox-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20spent%20campaign%20funds%20on%20OnlyFans%20and%20Botox%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20led%20to%20Santos's%20historic%20expulsion%20from%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20version%20of%20New%20York's%20%26quot%3BSon%20of%20Sam%26quot%3B%20law%20was%20passed%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20out%20of%20fear%20that%20the%20tabloid-famous%20serial%20killer%20would%20get%20a%20book%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20version%20of%20the%20law%20currently%20on%20the%20books%20is%20rarely%20invoked.%20The%20most%20prominent%20example%20in%20recent%20years%20is%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnetflix-paid-anna-delvey-sorokin-tv-series-victim-fund-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20state%20froze%20accounts%20belonging%20to%20Anna%20Sorokin%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20Anna%20Delvey%20%E2%80%94%20who%20had%20received%20%24320%2C000%20from%20Netflix%20for%20the%20rights%20to%20her%20life%20story%20after%20she%20operated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fanna-delvey-sorokin-art-show-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eher%20%26quot%3Bfake%20heiress%26quot%3B%20scam%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Authorities%20unfroze%20her%20assets%20once%20they%20verified%20she%20returned%20funds%20to%20the%20financial%20institutions%20she%20stole%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESantos%2C%20luckily%2C%20can%20make%20his%20Cameo%20videos%20unencumbered.%20Because%20he%20was%20charged%20by%20US%20Justice%20Department%20prosecutors%20under%20federal%20criminal%20statutes%2C%20he%20isn't%20affected%20by%20the%20state's%20%26quot%3BSon%20of%20Sam%26quot%3B%20law%2C%20experts%20on%20the%20law%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20the%20law%20requires%20a%20firm%20connection%20between%20the%20crime%20and%20the%20profit.%20Santos%20making%20money%20from%20his%20Cameo%20videos%20following%20his%20expulsion%20from%20Congress%20is%20a%20few%20degrees%20removed%20from%20the%20allegations%20described%20in%20the%2042-page%20federal%20indictment%20against%20him%2C%20according%20to%20Dmitriy%20Shakhnevich%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20John%20Jay%20College%20of%20Criminal%20Justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20nexus%20between%20a%20murderer%20going%20to%20jail%20for%20murder%2C%20and%20a%20congressman%20elected%20to%20Congress%20and%20then%20subsequently%20indicted%20for%20crimes%20that%20relate%20to%20his%20candidacy%2C%20are%20a%20little%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20Shakhnevich%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESantos's%20Cameo%20videos%20could%20cause%20trouble%20down%20the%20road%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20claim%20Santos%20committed%20a%20long%20list%20of%20misdeeds%2C%20including%20identity%20theft%2C%20credit%20card%20fraud%2C%20falsifying%20records%20submitted%20to%20Congress%2C%20and%20siphoning%20off%20campaign%20contributions%20for%20his%20personal%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20also%20notorious%20for%20a%20number%20of%20lies%20that%20are%20not%20necessarily%20part%20of%20the%20criminal%20charges%2C%20such%20as%20pretending%20he%20was%20on%20the%20Baruch%20College%20volleyball%20team%2C%20that%20his%20mother%20was%20at%20the%20World%20Trade%20Center%20on%209%2F11%2C%20and%20that%20he%20was%20an%20actor%20on%20%26quot%3BHannah%20Montana.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sheer%20range%20of%20contributions%20to%20Santos's%20notoriety%20would%20make%20it%20hard%20to%20argue%20that%20his%20Cameo%20money%20is%20directly%20derived%20from%20his%20alleged%20crimes%2C%20according%20to%20Matthew%20Mangino%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Luxenberg%2C%20Garbett%2C%20Kelly%2C%20and%20George.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMangino%20said%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20clear%20if%20Santos%20is%20capitalizing%20on%20his%20alleged%20fraud%20or%20his%20reputation%20as%20a%20terrible%20Congressman%20and%20liar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20little%20murkier%20than%2C%20say%2C%20some%20serial%20killer%20who%20murders%20eight%20people%2C%20and%20that's%20the%20reason%20for%20his%20notoriety%2C%20and%20he's%20out%20there%20trying%20to%20write%20a%20book%20or%20have%20a%20movie%20produced%2C%26quot%3B%20Mangino%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%E2%80%94%20the%20experts%20caution%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Cameo%20videos%20could%20cause%20trouble%20for%20Santos%20if%20he's%20found%20guilty%20and%20sentenced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20will%20be%20in%20federal%20court%20and%2C%20look%2C%20any%20lawyer%20worth%20his%20or%20her%20salt%20will%20tell%20a%20client%2C%20'Don't%20talk%20to%20anybody%20while%20you%20have%20a%20criminal%20case%20pending%20%E2%80%94%20and%20certainly%20don't%20do%20Cameos%2C'%26quot%3B%20Shakhnevich%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Santos%20wanted%20to%20make%20a%20plea%20deal%20with%20prosecutors%2C%20or%20is%20convicted%20in%20a%20trial%2C%20the%20videos%20could%20work%20against%20him.%20A%20judge%20could%20take%20them%20as%20evidence%20that%20he%20didn't%20take%20his%20conduct%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20Mangino%20said%2C%20it's%20too%20late%20for%20Santos%20to%20argue%20that%20expulsion%20from%20Congress%20was%20a%20bad%20enough%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20be%20tough%20to%20go%20in%20front%20of%20a%20judge%20if%20he's%20being%20sentenced%20and%20ask%20for%20some%20mitigation%20when%20he%20hasn't%20really%20taken%20the%20whole%20process%20seriously%2C%20and%20that%20he%20tried%20to%20profit%20by%20getting%20expelled%20from%20Congress%2C%26quot%3B%20Mangino%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20don't%20see%20how%20this%20won't%20be%20bad%20for%20him%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorge-santos-cameo-money-son-of-sam-law-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702034941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657231927a3c8094d5dac98f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https