sian%20president%20Vladimir%20Putin%20announces%20his%20intention%20to%20run%20for%20the%202024%20presidential%20election%2C%20ensuring%20his%20stay%20in%20power%20until%20at%20least%202030.%20Despite%20the%20costly%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20attacks%20within%20Russia%2C%20Putin%20maintains%20strong%20support.%20The%20election%20will%20be%20held%20over%20three%20days%20in%20March%202024.%20With%20opposition%20politician%20Alexei%20Navalny%20imprisoned%20and%20critics%20silenced%2C%20Putin%20faces%20no%20significant%20political%20competition.%20In%20April%202021%2C%20Putin%20signed%20constitutional%20amendments%20allowing%20him%20to%20seek%20reelection%20twice%20more%2C%20potentially%20extending%20his%20presidency%20to%202036.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20WORLD%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fvladimir-putin-to-run-for-president-again-in-2024-elections%2Farticleshow%2F105841663.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Suitcases%20Out%2C%20Laptops%20In%20-%20The%20Death%20Of%20Lobbying%20In%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20time%20in%20the%20Indian%20capital%20when%20lobbyists%20could%20influence%20and%20seal%20deals%20to%20suit%20their%20masters.%20And%20politicians%20would%20eat%20out%20of%20their%20hands.%20Those%20were%20the%20heady%20days%20of%20lobbying%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20liquor%20baron%20Vijay%20Mallya%2C%20now%20in%20exile%2C%20took%20lobbying%20to%20a%20new%20level.%20He%20took%20to%20carting%20the%20high%20and%20mighty%20on%20weekend%20binges.%20His%20private%20jets%20were%20tweaked%20to%20accommodate%20bureaucrats%2C%20politicians%20and%20influential%20persons%2C%20all%20given%20seven-star%20accommodation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20an%20IAS%20officer%20who%2C%20as%20a%20top%20shot%20of%20Air%20India%2C%20gave%20unlimited-go-anywhere-in-the-world%20business%20class%20cards%20to%20his%20IAS%20colleagues%20and%20selected%20political%20bosses.%20Who%20utilised%20the%20cards%20is%20still%20a%20locked%20secret%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Civil%20Aviation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20was%20a%20champion%20lobbyist%2C%20the%20top%20honcho%20of%20a%20premier%20hospital.%20He%20had%20tremendous%20clout%2C%20thanks%20to%20free%20medical%20treatment%20he%20offered.%20He%20was%20the%20smartest%20fixer%3B%20he%20could%20fix%20anything%20in%20the%20corridors%20of%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20were%20so%20powerful%20that%20they%20could%20drum%20up%20support%20from%20over%20150%20MPs%20across%20party%20lines%20to%20raise%20in%20Parliament%2C%20even%20get%20finance%20ministry%20officials%20copy-paste%20some%20of%20their%20companies'%20pre-budget%20recommendations%20into%20the%20final%20budget%20speech.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20influencers%20felt%20they%20were%20powerful.%20Like%20a%20steel%20baron%20who%20walked%20in%20the%20corridors%20of%20various%20ministries%20with%20a%20full%20entourage%2C%20including%20a%20person%20right%20behind%20him%20to%20catch%20his%20jacket%20the%20moment%20it%20was%20flung%20backwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20were%20the%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20the%20days%20of%20surreptitious%20meetings%20with%20spooks%2C%20officials%20and%20reporters%20in%20cafes%20are%20nearly%20over%2C%20except%20for%20a%20handful%20of%20the%20old%20school%20mavericks%20who%20have%20survived%20the%20digital%20age%20and%20changes%20to%20the%20way%20the%20government%20operated%20since%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20few%20want%20to%20gain%20political%20influence%20in%20India.%20Now%2C%20no%20one%20splurges%20cash%2C%20gold%20biscuits%2C%20gold%20coins%20or%20gold%20ganeshas%20during%20Diwali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20many%20can't%20dig%20foxholes%20like%20the%20old%20days.%20NDA%20is%20like%20Fort%20Knox%2C%20you%20just%20cannot%20walk%20in.%20You%20need%20solid%20connections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENowadays%2C%20the%20government%20does%20not%20even%20care%20to%20issue%20circulars%20about%20stopping%20%3Cem%3Eundesirable%20people%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20ministries.%20Secretaries%20of%20ministers%20who%20were%20%26quot%3Bfriendly%26quot%3B%20have%20flown%2C%20so%20special%20meetings%20cannot%20be%20arranged.%20Hence%2C%20there%20is%20no%20friendly%20banter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20to%20do%20business%20with%20the%20government%20then%20things%20need%20to%20be%20super%20transparent%2C%20I%20would%20involve%20as%20many%20stakeholders%20so%20that%20everyone%20would%20know%20what%20is%20happening%20on%20the%20table%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Deepak%20Talwar%2C%20a%20former%20lobbyist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20does%20lobbying%20happen%3F%20Many%20seek%20help%20from%20the%20ideological%20founts%20of%20people%20who%20flock%20the%20corridors%20of%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20not%20to%20say%20the%20political%20advocacy%20people%20are%20out%20of%20work.%20This%20brigade%20comes%20in%20handy%20when%20elections%20are%20round%20and%20ticket-seekers%20need%20help.%20These%20lobbyists%20open%20doors%20to%20top%20RSS%20brass%20or%20top%20BJP%20leaders%20who%20can%20genuinely%20swing%20the%20tickets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20political%2C%20and%20there%20is%20corporate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELobbyists%20in%20the%20form%20of%20several%20legal%20firms%20and%20advocacy%20firms%20were%20active%20when%20gaming%20companies%20were%20saddled%20with%20a%2028%20percent%20GST.%20They%20held%20routine%20meetings%20with%20officials%20of%20the%20Finance%20Ministry%2C%20explaining%20why%20the%20tax%20structure%20would%20not%20stand%20a%20chance%20in%20the%20courts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20Finance%20Ministry%20did%20not%20budge.%20Exasperated%2C%20a%20senior%20official%20of%20a%20gaming%20company%20even%20told%20a%20top%20official%3A%20%26quot%3BLooks%20like%20you%20people%20are%20conjuring%20up%20some%20magical%20sum%20(of%20Rs%20100%2C000%20crores)%20from%20three%20gaming%20companies%20only%20because%20the%20divestment%20target%20of%20the%20annual%20budget%20has%20not%20been%20met.%26quot%3B%20The%20Finance%20Ministry%20official%20did%20not%20reply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20happened%20when%20a%20host%20of%20oil%20companies%20lobbied%20hard%20to%20bureaucrats%20to%20drop%20the%20windfall%20gain%20tax%20from%20petroleum%20products.%20That%20also%20did%20not%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuitcases%20are%20out%2C%20laptops%20are%20in.%20Influence%20peddling%20has%20been%20replaced%20with%20intense%20confabulations%20and%20the%20power%20broker%20has%20been%20replaced%20with%20powerpoints%2C%20at%20least%20at%20the%20Centre.%20Good%20practitioners%20today%20rely%20more%20on%20data%20and%20arguments%20and%20there%20is%20less%20discretionary%20arbitrage%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Supriyo%20Gupta%20of%20Torque%2C%20a%20communications%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%20lobbying%20works%2C%20as%20happened%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20government's%20move%20to%20push%20the%20controversial%20Tax%20Collected%20At%20Source%20(TCS).%20The%20government%2C%20in%20the%20face%20of%20some%20solid%20lobbying%20and%20media%20advocacy%2C%20backtracked%20and%20kept%20the%20plan%20on%20the%20backburner.%20For%20the%20lobbyists%2C%20putting%20things%20on%20the%20backburner%20is%20considered%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELobbyists%20work%20in%20all%20kinds%20of%20environments.%20Some%20moons%20ago%2C%20big%20guns%20of%20the%20liquor%20business%20met%20for%20five%20days%20in%20the%20Lodhi%20Hotel%20to%20discuss%20ways%20to%20dominate%20Delhi's%20liquor%20business.%20But%20the%20scam%20exploded%20and%20ended%20with%20some%20high-profile%20arrests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20old-school%20people%20too%20have%20adopted%20a%20hybrid%20mode%20of%20operations%2C%20swinging%20between%20the%20old%20systems%20of%20plugging%20stories%20to%20reporters%20and%20the%20new%20ways%20of%20lobbying%20for%20their%20corporate%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20few%20takers%20for%20the%20print%20media%2C%20or%20the%20media%20in%20general.%20Some%20lobbyists%20push%20out%20stories%20to%20the%20print%20media%20so%20as%20to%20make%20sure%20there%20are%20no%20loopholes%2C%20they%20call%20it%20media%20advocacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20leap%20is%20now%20on%20social%20media.%20Lobbyists%20spend%20more%20time%20on%20social%20media%20themselves%2C%20boosting%20their%20own%20profile%20as%20well%20as%20keeping%20a%20track%20of%20influencers%20in%20their%20sphere%20of%20work.%20Some%20of%20the%20most%20influential%20are%20the%20YouTubers%2C%20and%20some%20of%20those%20who%20seem%20to%20work%20without%20any%20influence%20are%20also%20malleable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenefits%20previously%20reserved%20for%20reporters%20now%20are%20directed%20to%20YouTube%20influencers%20which%20have%20left%20some%20journalists%20unhappy%2C%20and%20also%20upset%20with%20the%20lack%20of%20press%20junkets.%20Some%20lobbyists%20have%20been%20known%20to%20use%20bots%20to%20ramp%20up%20the%20social%20media%20presence%20of%20their%20clients.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Board%20of%20India%20(SEBI)%20has%20often%20issued%20warnings%20against%20such%20influencers%20who%20would%20often%20peddle%20stocks%20of%20all%20kinds.%20Some%20of%20the%20companies%20employ%20entrepreneurs%20who%20specialise%20in%20this.%20An%20example%20for%20both%20of%20these%20is%20the%20auto%20sector.%20There%20are%20rarely%20any%20negative%20reviews%20of%20automobiles%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20every%20corporation%20is%20releasing%20products%20that%20are%20very%20similar%20to%20each%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20influencers%20are%20given%20early%20access%20to%20vehicles%2C%20sneak%20peeks%20and%20lots%20of%20gifts%20based%20on%20their%20viewer%20counts%20and%20engagements.%20Company%20social%20media%20handles%20are%20boosted%20by%20enterprises%20that%20use%20WhatsApp%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20large%20number%20of%20unemployed%20youths%20with%20smartphones.%20They%20are%20both%20consumers%20of%20these%20social%20media%20plugs%20as%20well%20as%20people%20who%20can%20be%20paid%20to%20subscribe%20to%20channels%20and%20engage%20with%20the%20content%20on%20them.%20Each%20subscription%20or%20'like'%20gets%20Rs%20100.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi-centric%20deal-making%20has%20decreased%2C%20opening%20up%20opportunities%20for%20lobbyists%20from%20across%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20also%20because%20influencing%20bureaucrats%20is%20not%20as%20easy%20as%20it%20used%20to%20be%20earlier%2C%20there%20is%20a%20close%20watch%20on%20who%20is%20coming%20to%20meet%20with%20officials%20and%20why%20to%20diminish%20chances%20of%20corruption%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPaid%20junkets%20for%20bureaucrats%20are%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past.%20There%20are%20no%20more%20business%20class%20flights%2C%20even%20silent%20upgrades%20inside%20the%20aircraft%20have%20gone%20for%20a%20toss.%20There%20is%20always%20a%20trail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20is%20the%20way%20out%3F%20Take%20some%20hard%20calls.%20Why%20not%20plug%20a%20Brazil-Argentina%20semi-final%20to%20be%20watched%20from%20the%20corporate%20box%2C%20or%20a%20Grand%20Prix%20from%20the%20balcony%20of%20the%20hotel%20in%20Singapore%3F%20Take%20a%20bunch%20for%20a%20darshan%20of%20the%20Lal%20Baugh%20Cha%20Raja%20Ganesha%20in%20Mumbai.%20Remember%20how%20a%20fugitive%20diamond%20merchant%20some%20years%20ago%20had%20rented%20a%20private%20jet%20and%20asked%20bureaucrats%20of%20the%20Commerce%20Ministry%20to%20take%20a%20ride%20for%20a%20special%20darshan%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20hasn't%20changed%20is%20the%20'entertainment%20expense'%20column%20in%20the%20daily%20ledger.%20Lobbyists%20still%20take%20out%20pals%20for%20drinks%2C%20scoping%20for%20the%20odd%20bit%20of%20corporate%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20contemplated%20using%20tech%20surveillance%20to%20keep%20a%20tab%20on%20what%20their%20competitors%20are%20up%20to.%20Which%20is%20why%20some%20lobbyists%20are%20very%20careful%20as%20to%20what%20they%20say%20on%20their%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20them%20have%20become%20digital%20savvy.%20They%20only%20use%20data%20calls%20and%20apps%20such%20as%20Telegram%20and%20FaceTime%20to%20make%20calls%20to%20set%20up%20meetings%20and%20avoid%20detailed%20discussions%20on%20those%20apps%20that%20were%20avoidable.%20This%20started%20after%20the%20Radia%20Tapes%20but%20was%20amplified%20by%20the%20Pegasus%20scandals.%20And%20now%2C%20there%20is%20much%20cheaper%20malware%20available%20from%20shady%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20work%20cannot%20stop%2C%20right%3F%20So%2C%20make%20the%20work%20look%20like%20the%20perfect%20corporate%20social%20responsibility.%20It%20will%20please%20the%20masters.%20That%20means%2075%2C000%20sewing%20machines%2C%2010%20lakh%20bicycles%2C%20100%20ambulances%2C%20leaders%20ranging%20from%20a%20bunch%20of%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20multinationals%20go%20a%20step%20forward%2C%20creating%20a%20special%20home%20to%20showcase%20instruments%20of%20legends%2C%20say%20the%20shehnai%20of%20the%20legendary%20Bismillah%20Khan%20at%20a%20museum%20in%20Varanasi.%20They%20are%20all%20in%20the%20pleasing%20business.%20The%20list%20is%20endless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20prefer%20the%20PPP%20model.%20Gaming%20companies%20were%20encouraged%20to%20spend%20cash%20on%20stadiums%20built%20by%20the%20government%20but%20now%20in%20a%20dilapidated%20condition.%20Costs%20hover%20between%20Rs%201.5-2%20crore%20per%20annum.%20It%20pleases%20the%20politicians%20who%20can%20use%20the%20stadium%20for%20football%2C%20cricket%2C%20or%20more%20importantly%2C%20political%20rallies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompanies%20seeking%20direct%20policy%20changes%20often%20let%20promoters%20talk%20directly%20to%20the%20people%20in%20power.%20Some%20of%20their%20corporate%20honchos%20even%20land%20up%20at%20events%20attended%20by%20hundreds%20but%20still%20manage%20to%20get%20some%20private%20moments%20from%20a%20minister.%20And%20then%20there%20is%20scope%20to%20exchange%20pleasantries%20during%20festivals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20civilised%20lobbying%2C%20and%20uncivilised%20lobbying.%20The%20first%20is%20the%20Washington-way.%20The%20second%20-%20mostly%20plantation%20and%20mining%20companies%20-%20is%20very%20crass.%20They%20do%20things%20openly.%20Sterlite%20Power%20lobbied%20hard%20to%20open%20the%20Thothakuddi%20plant%2C%20arguing%20the%20closure%20is%20all%20political%20and%20less%20environmental.%20But%20it%20still%20did%20not%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETop%20sources%20say%20some%20of%20the%20important%20companies%20include%20Koan%20Advisory%2C%20Dialogue%2C%20Primus%2C%20Chase%2C%20DeepStart%20and%20Aakhya.%20There%20is%20also%20Brunswick%2C%20FTI%20Consulting%20and%20APCO%20Worldwide.%20Manu%20Kapoor%2C%20former%20Samsung%20big%20shot%2C%20is%20a%20seasoned%20campaigner.%20And%20there%20is%20Mukesh%20Aghi%2C%20the%20President%20and%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20the%20US-India%20Strategic%20Partnership%20Forum%20whose%20favourite%20lines%20are%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20India%20grows%2C%20the%20world%20grows%20too.%26quot%3B%20There%20are%20some%20journalists%20too%20in%20the%20game%2C%20one%20from%20Gujarat%20and%20a%20television%20journalist%20from%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20Both%20are%20considered%20powerful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20age%20lobbyists%20are%20doing%20their%20work%2C%20minus%20cash%2C%20gold%20or%20Khan%20Market%20coffee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Shantanu%20Guha%20Ray%20is%20the%20Asia%20Editor%20of%20Central%20European%20News%2C%20UK.%20His%20book%20on%20coal%2C%20Black%20Harvest%2C%20will%20hit%20the%20stands%20soon)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702034700