e%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20immigrants%20entering%20the%20state%20without%20documents.%20The%20section%20allows%20foreign%20migrants%20to%20become%20Indian%20citizens%20if%20they%20had%20entered%20Assam%20till%20January%201%2C%201966%2C%20adding%20the%20provision%20that%20those%20who%20had%20entered%20after%20that%20date%20till%20March%2024%2C%201971%2C%20should%20also%20be%20considered%20for%20citizenship%20provided%20they%20are%20registered%20and%20their%20voting%20rights%20deferred%20for%20two%20consecutive%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20several%20petitions%20are%20in%20support%20of%20the%20section%20approved%20by%20Parliament%2C%20some%20others%20are%20opposed%20to%20it%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20there%20should%20be%20a%20common%20citizenship%20rule%20for%20the%20entire%20country%2C%20and%20allowing%20such%20immigrants%20to%20become%20citizens%20and%20voters%20in%20Assam%20would%20change%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20demography%20and%20thereby%20affect%20the%20local%20community%E2%80%99s%20culture%2C%20language%20and%20political%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20day%20one%20of%20the%20hearing%20on%20December%205%2C%20the%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20had%20orally%20observed%20that%20the%20special%20section%20was%20enacted%20by%20Parliament%20for%20Assam%20considering%20humanitarian%20aspects%20due%20to%20the%20Liberation%20War%20of%20Bangladesh%20with%20which%20the%20north-eastern%20state%20shares%20a%20long%20border.%20The%20chief%20justice%20said%20it%20had%20to%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20vital%20role%20that%20India%20played%20in%20the%20liberation%20of%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20had%20stated%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20that%20liberation%20movement%20seems%20to%20have%20led%20Parliament%20proceed%20on%20the%20basis%20that%20the%20immigration%20that%20took%20place%20due%20to%20it%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20purely%20be%20regarded%20as%20illegal%20but%20humanitarian.%20The%20constitutional%20bench%20also%20includes%20Justices%20Surya%20Kant%2C%20M.M.%20Sundresh%2C%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20then%20asked%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20Tushar%20Mehta%20to%20provide%20details%20on%20how%20many%20people%20had%20benefitted%20from%20the%20section%20since%20its%20enactment%2C%20also%20noting%20that%20it%20has%20nothing%20in%20front%20of%20it%20to%20deduce%20that%20the%20cultural%20rights%20of%20the%20people%20were%20affected%20by%20such%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20had%20orally%20remarked%20that%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20must%20be%20given%20some%20leeway%20to%20make%20compromises%20for%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20wellbeing%20and%20that%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20judged%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20hindsight%20wisdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202014%2C%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20framed%2013%20questions%20encompassing%20various%20issues%20around%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20Section%206A%2C%20including%20whether%20the%20cultural%20and%20political%20rights%20of%20the%20Assamese%20people%20were%20diluted%20by%20the%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20the%20bench%20referred%20the%20case%20to%20a%20five-judge%20constitutional%20bench%20which%20has%20resumed%20the%20hearing%20early%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20of%20the%20case%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20country%20is%20close%20to%20the%202024%20parliamentary%20elections%20when%20Narendra%20Modi%20would%20be%20seeking%20a%20third%20term.%20In%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%202014%20and%202019%20polls%2C%20the%20alleged%20threat%20of%20%E2%80%98illegal%20immigrants%E2%80%99%20(read%20Muslims%20from%20Bangladesh)%20on%20Assam%20and%20Bengal%20and%20the%20need%20for%20a%20provision%20in%20the%20Act%20to%20protect%20and%20grant%20citizenship%20to%20three%20groups%20of%20people%20including%20Hindus%20from%20Bangladesh%20in%20Assam%20and%20elsewhere%20were%20used%20as%20political%20tools%20by%20the%20ruling%20party%20during%20its%20campaigning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20two%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20ministers%20have%20reiterated%20that%20rules%20to%20implement%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%20would%20be%20readied%20soon.%20This%20special%20provision%20is%20likely%20to%20come%20to%20the%20aid%20of%20a%20large%20swathe%20of%20voters%20across%20Bengal%20and%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702030523000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fassam-citizenship-case-sc-tells-union-govt-to-give-details-on-undocumented-immigrants-in-northeast%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20directives%20have%20come%20during%20the%20hearing%20of%20a%20bunch%20of%20petitions%20opposed%20to%2C%20and%20in%20support%20of%2C%20Section%206A%20inserted%20into%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%201955%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20Parliament%20for%20the%20state%20of%20Assam.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fassam-citizenship-case-sc-tells-union-govt-to-give-details-on-undocumented-immigrants-in-northeast%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20startups'%20funding%20winter%20persists%2C%2072%25%20decline%20in%202023%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702030487000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-04%2F17%2Ffull%2F1650215095-91.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Findian-startups-funding-winter-persists-72-decline-in-2023-report-123120800692_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20highlighted%20that%20the%20