Maharashtra%20reported%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20human%20deaths%20due%20to%20tiger%20attacks%20in%202022%20at%2085.%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20reported%20the%20second-highest%20number%20of%20deaths%20at%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20deaths%20due%20to%20elephant%20attacks%2C%20Odisha%20reported%20the%20highest%20number%20in%202022-2023%20at%20148.%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Jharkhand%20and%20Assam%20were%20next%20with%2097%2C%2096%20and%2080%20deaths%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20293%20people%20died%20due%20to%20tiger%20attacks%20and%202%2C657%20people%20died%20to%20elephant%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinister%20of%20state%20Ashwini%20Kumar%20Choubey%20provided%20the%20data%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20from%20Jebi%20Mather%20Hisham%2C%20a%20Congress%20party%20MP%20from%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHisham%20had%20asked%20whether%20the%20environment%20ministry%20complies%20state%20or%20Union%20territory-level%20data%20on%20%E2%80%9Chuman-wildlife%20encounters%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChoubey%20replied%20saying%20that%20state%20and%20Union%20territory%20governments%20primarily%20manage%20and%20protect%20wildlife.%20He%20provided%20the%20available%20data%20on%20human%20deaths%20due%20to%20tiger%20and%20elephant%20attacks%20as%20reported%20by%20these%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20reply%20did%20not%20say%20why%20deaths%20due%20to%20attacks%20by%20other%20animals%20did%20not%20figure%20in%20the%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20by%20Hisham%20for%20state-level%20data%20on%20how%20the%20loss%20of%20human%20lives%2C%20livestock%20and%20crops%20due%20to%20wildlife%20encounters%20were%20being%20compensated%20for%2C%20Choubey%20said%20the%20environment%20ministry%20did%20not%20collate%20this%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20states%2FUnion%20territories%20make%20ex-gratia%20payments%20for%20loss%20of%20livestock%2C%20crops%20and%20human%20life%20including%20injuries%20due%20to%20human-wildlife%20conflicts%20as%20per%20the%20norms%20which%20vary%20from%20state%20to%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%202021%20study%20on%20human-wildlife%20conflict%20said%20that%20at%20the%20time%2C%20the%20average%20compensation%20paid%20in%20India%20for%20human%20deaths%20was%20Rs%201%2C91%2C437.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumit%20Gulati%2C%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20study%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fto-manage-human-wildlife-conflict-compensation-for-human-casualties-a-must%2F%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20increasing%20compensation%20for%20human%20victims%20of%20such%20conflict%20would%20reduce%20feelings%20of%20animosity%20toward%20wild%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20governments%20invested%20in%20measures%20to%20reduce%20conflict%20based%20on%20an%20accurate%20understanding%20of%20the%20real%20value%20of%20the%20loss%20of%20human%20life%2C%20conflict%20would%20be%20reduced%2C%20and%20animosity%20would%20fall%2C%20making%20both%20those%20living%20near%20the%20forest%20and%20those%20who%20care%20about%20the%20beings%20in%20the%20forest%20better%20off%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gulati%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aninews.in%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgeneral-news%2Futtarakhand-cabinet-gives-nod-to-human-wildlife-conflict-relief-distribution-rule20230825060916%2F%5C%22%3ESeveral%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fothers%2Fodisha-government-increases-compensation-for-human-wildlife-conflict-livestock-loss-and-crop-damage-101683124650808.html%5C%22%3Estates%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ftelangana%2Fstate-wildlife-board-okays-increased-compensation%2Farticle66505044.ece%5C%22%3Ehave%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fjharkhand-to-hike-compensation-for-victims-of-attack-by-wild-animals%2F1605162%2F%5C%22%3Esince%3C%2Fa%3E%20decided%20to%20increase%20the%20compensation%20they%20provide%20to%20human%20victims%20of%20such%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHisham%20also%20asked%20what%20measures%20the%20government%20proposed%20to%20take%20in%20light%20of%20what%20she%20said%20was%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20animal%20attacks%20due%20to%20their%20growing%20population%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20resulting%20%E2%80%9Cdecrease%20in%20informal%20players%E2%80%99%20reliance%20on%20forest%20resources%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChoubey%20said%20that%20measures%20taken%20by%20the%20government%20include%20issuing%20advisories%20to%20state%20governments%20on%20managing%20wildlife%2C%20including%20species-specific%20ones%20on%20mitigating%20conflict%20with%20humans%3B%20establishing%20wildlife%20sanctuaries%3B%20and%20providing%20financial%20assistance%20to%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20assistance%20is%20provided%20under%20schemes%20which%20support%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconstruction%2Ferection%20of%20physical%20barriers%20such%20as%20barbed%20wire%20fence%2C%20solar-powered%20electric%20fence%2C%20bio-fencing%20using%20cactus%2C%20boundary%20walls%20etc.%20to%20prevent%20the%20entry%20of%20wild%20animals%20into%20crop%20fields%2C%E2%80%9D%20Choubey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702024244000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08121728%2FFotoJet.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Ftiger-elephant-attack-deaths-data-parliament%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Minister%20of%20state%20in%20the%20Union%20environment%20ministry%20Ashwini%20Kumar%20Choubey%20told%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20that%20the%20ministry%20does%20not%20collate%20information%20on%20how%20state%20and%20UT%20governments%20compensate%20deaths%20and%20injuries%20due%20to%20human-wildlife%20conflict.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvir