n.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08140547%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-12-08-at-1.55.37-PM.jpeg%20978w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08140547%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-12-08-at-1.55.37-PM-245x300.jpeg%20245w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08140547%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-12-08-at-1.55.37-PM-835x1024.jpeg%20835w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688296%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22604%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChowdhury%20requested%20as%20much%20during%20the%20discussion%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20too.%20Congress%20MP%20Manish%20Tiwari%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CToday%20we%20are%20sitting%20as%20a%20court%20to%20judge%20our%20colleague%2C%20this%20is%20not%20a%20parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20Speaker%20Birla%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20parliament%2C%20not%20the%20judge.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20leaders%20of%20the%20opposition%2C%20including%20those%20from%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20party%20TMC%2C%20expressed%20grave%20opposition%20to%20the%20report%20outside%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPTI%20reported%20TMC%20MP%20Sudip%20Bandyopadhyay%20as%20having%20noted%20that%20he%20had%20a%20one-on-one%20meeting%20with%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20on%20this%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20told%20the%20Speaker%20that%20Moitra%20should%20be%20given%20time%20to%20make%20her%20speech%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20house%20to%20which%20Birla%20replied%20that%20half%20an%20hour%20would%20be%20given%20for%20discussion%20on%20the%20matter%2C%E2%80%9D%20PTI%20said%2C%20of%20Bandyopadhyay%2C%20who%20also%20questioned%20why%20the%20MP%20who%20alleged%20that%20Moitra%20was%20paid%20cash%20for%20asking%20questions%20%E2%80%93%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Nishikant%20Dubey%20%E2%80%93%20not%20called%20to%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDubey%20and%20Supreme%20Court%20lawyer%20Jai%20Anant%20Dehadrai%20had%20alleged%20that%20Moitra%20accepted%20cash%20and%20gifts%20from%20businessman%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20as%20bribes%20for%20asking%20questions%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Moitra%20has%20denied%20these%20allegations%2C%20deeming%20them%20%E2%80%9Ccompletely%20baseless.%E2%80%9D%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20request%20that%20the%20committee%20summon%20Hiranandani%20and%20allow%20her%20to%20cross-examine%20him%20and%20Dehadrai%20were%20turned%20down%20by%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%E2%80%99s%20report%20called%20out%20Moitra%20for%20%E2%80%9Cunethical%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccontempt%20of%20the%20House%E2%80%9D%20for%20sharing%20her%20Lok%20Sabha%20log-in%20credentials%20with%20Hiranandani%2C%20which%20Moitra%20countered%20by%20saying%20that%20house%20members%20frequently%20share%20their%20credentials%20with%20interns%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fparliamentary-ethics-committee-opposition-mps-mahua-moitra%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20noted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20committee%2C%20headed%20by%20BJP%20MP%20Vinod%20Kumar%20Sonkar%2C%20has%20been%20criticised%20because%20of%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20its%20meetings%20were%20conducted%20as%20well.%20One%20such%20meeting%20ended%20in%20a%20walkout%C2%A0not%20just%20by%20Moitra%20but%20also%20by%20five%20members%20of%20the%20opposition%20parties.%20%E2%80%9CShe%20was%20asked%20which%20hotel%20in%20Dubai%20she%20had%20stayed%20during%20her%20visits%20and%20with%20whom%2C%20etc.%20Opposition%20members%20found%20those%20questions%20posed%20to%20a%20woman%20member%20of%20parliament%20in%20an%20official%20platform%20very%20offensive%20and%20walked%20out%20of%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20opposition%20MP%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20day%20began%2C%20Moitra%20told%20the%20news%20agency%20ANI%20in%20Hindi%20that%20Durga%20had%20arrived.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20shall%20see%20now